### Version
2.7.0

### Reproduction link
[https://github.com/vuejs/vue-hackernews-2.0](https://github.com/vuejs/vue-hackernews-2.0)

### Steps to reproduce
1. git clone https://github.com/vuejs/vue-hackernews-2.0
2. npm i
3. add `beforeRouteEnter` event to `src/views/CreateListView.js`:
```js
  beforeRouteEnter(to, from, next) {
    next((vm) => {
      console.log('before enter user view');
    });
  }
```
4. add `console.log` to `vue-router.common.js` line `2058`:
```js
function poll (
  cb, // somehow flow cannot infer this is a function
  instances,
  key,
  isValid
) {
  if (instances[key]) {
    cb(instances[key]);
  } else if (isValid()) {
    setTimeout(function () {
      console.log('vue-router poll');
      poll(cb, instances, key, isValid);
    }, 16);
  }
}
```
5. npm run dev
6. open `http://127.0.0.1:8080/`

### What is expected?
memory can be gc collected

### What is actually happening?
memory and cpu grow up, and it keeps printing `vue-router poll`


